Base.Explanation: Get the primary group for an Active Directory object (user, computer, group, etc.).

ArrayElement.Name: Active Directory object
ArrayElement.Description: A data structure representing the Active Directory object for which the primary group is obtained. The property must be specified as a variable, for which the value is determined in a previously executed script action.

ArrayElement.Name: Primary group name
ArrayElement.Description: The value found for the primary group. This property is an 'output only' property and is generated by the application automatically. By default, the value for this property is stored in variable %PrimaryGroupName%.

Base.FunctionDescription: Replace all occurences of the specified source substring by the specified target substring.
